    <name>
      <text>Operation of complex number using conjugate property</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Write the complex number  \(z = \displaystyle  \frac{({@a1@})+({@a2@})}{({@b1@})-({@b2@})}\)   in the form \(a+b{@%i@}\). </p>
<p><em>Note: Use <code>b*%i</code> to input the imaginary part of the complex number.</p>
<p> \(z =\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked solution</h3>
<p>\(
\begin{align}
 \displaystyle  z & =  \frac{({@a1@})+({@a2@})}{({@b1@})-({@b2@})} \\
& =  \displaystyle \frac{@aa@}{@bb@} \\
& =  \displaystyle \left( \frac{@aa@}{@bb@} \right) \left( \frac{\overline{@bb@}}{\overline{@bb@}} \right) \\
& =  \displaystyle \left( \frac{@aa@}{@bb@} \right) \left( \frac{@conj@}{@conj@}\right)\\
& =   \displaystyle \frac{@ta1@}{@ta2@} \\
& = \displaystyle  {@rez@}{@if imagpart(tt)<0 then "-" else "+"@}{@abs(imagpart(tt))@}{@%i@}
\end{align}
\)</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
